: [{\"ngram\": \"Danis Civil\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1128}, {\"ngram\": \"the moniker Dany Dann\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1178}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"Kissimmmee\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1233}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1258}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the women's side, Ami Yuasa of Japan captured the gold, Dominika Banevi\\u010d of Lithuania seized the silver medal, and Liu Qingyi of China won bronze.\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.5471801772544351, \"rank\": 0.82753105122121, \"text\": \"Lithuania\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1382, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qingyi_River_(Sichuan)\", \"score\": 0.6010059089230338, \"rank\": 0.4444444444445492, \"text\": \"Qingyi\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qingyi_River_(Sichuan)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qingyi_River_(Sichuan)\"}, {\"begin\": 1392, \"end\": 1397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9715076309825048, \"rank\": 0.02931541579756566, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the women's side\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"Ami Yuasa\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"Japan\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"Dominika Banevi\\u010d\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver medal\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1372}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1408}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opinions about breakdancing in the Olympics, which as of now is not slated to be at the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics, varied, from being praised to criticized as being not worthy of an Olympic sporting event.\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1616, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Opinions\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1419}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic sporting event\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1615}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheAmsterdam Newsspoke exclusively with world-renown breakdancer Jorge \\\"Popmaster Fabel\\\" Pabon, who began his career in the early 1980s and was featured in the pioneering hip-hop cult classic film \\\"Beat Street,\\\" about the physical and mental skills it takes to be an elite breakdancer and his thoughts on it genre as an Olympic competition.\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1690, \"end\": 1699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PopMaster\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Popmaster\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PopMaster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PopMaster\"}, {\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dorlan_Pab\\u00f3n\", \"score\": 0.9753060709547242, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pabon\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dorlan_Pab\\u00f3n\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dorlan_Pab\\u00f3n\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"TheAmsterdam Newsspoke\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1640}, {\"ngram\": \"his career\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"the early 1980s\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1753}, {\"ngram\": \"the pioneering hip-hop cult classic film\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1814}, {\"ngram\": \"Beat Street\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 1827}, {\"ngram\": \"the physical and mental skills\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1866}, {\"ngram\": \"an elite breakdancer\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1902}, {\"ngram\": \"his thoughts\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1919}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic competition\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1957}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Any B-girl, B-boy, rocker or breaker that has the aim to compete at the highest levels needs to learn the history of the dance, first and foremost,\\\" said Pabon, who has taught popping and locking at workshops globally and for the past 25 years at New York University's Tisch School of the Arts.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 2255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2208, \"end\": 2227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_University\", \"score\": 0.9999614215873582, \"rank\": 3.857990108615417e-05, \"text\": \"New York University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_University\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Any B-girl\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"B-boy\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"rocker\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 1986}, {\"ngram\": \"breaker\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 1997}, {\"ngram\": \"the aim\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2014}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest levels\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2047}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"the dance\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2087}, {\"ngram\": \"Pabon\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2120}, {\"ngram\": \"popping\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2144}, {\"ngram\": \"workshops\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2169}, {\"ngram\": \"the past 25 years\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"the Arts\", \"from\": 2246, \"to\": 2254}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Secondly, they should cross-train mentally, spiritually, and physically.\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Learning the foundational dance steps, techniques and moves is not enough to be a top competitor.\\\"\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2428, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the foundational dance steps\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"techniques\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2379}, {\"ngram\": \"moves\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2389}, {\"ngram\": \"a top competitor\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2426}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pabon noted that aspiring breakdancers should consider learning the roots and history of certain African and Indigenous dance forms.\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pabon\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"aspiring breakdancers\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2468}, {\"ngram\": \"the roots\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2503}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2515}, {\"ngram\": \"certain African and Indigenous dance forms\", \"from\": 2519, \"to\": 2561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"West African dances such as the Nigerian dances of the Orishas and Senegalese cultural dance forms, Native American dance forms such as grass dances and other well-grounded movements, Afro-Caribbean dance forms such as Puerto Rican/Boriken and Cuban, Rhumba, Mambo, Bomba, Plena and Salsa, [as well as] American Black dances such as the Jitterbug/Lindy Hop, Huffing/Tap dance, [and] James Brown's Good Foot.\\\"\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2597, \"end\": 2605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\", \"score\": 0.9995865008445637, \"rank\": 0.0004135580160105426, \"text\": \"Nigerian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\"}, {\"begin\": 2620, \"end\": 2627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orishas_(band)\", \"score\": 0.9900245211738039, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Orishas\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://d